    "discriminators": [
     "The most distinctive signature in the material set: an explosive high-frequency burst (very high crest_factor, high_band_energy > 0.5, centroid often above 5 kHz) followed immediately by a DENSE tinkling debris TEXTURE - shards landing at a high onset_rate_per_second and decaying away. Burst-then-texture in one file.",
     "Against GLASS-IMPACT: an impact leaves the object whole - one bright ring, transient_count near 1, no shard shower.",
     "Against GLASS-CRASH & DEBRIS: BREAK is a singular failure (one bottle, one window) front-loaded on one violent burst; CRASH & DEBRIS is multiple items / loose shards with onsets spread across the file (higher envelope_temporal_centroid, lower peak crest_factor).",
     "Against CERAMICS-BREAK: same morphology, but ceramics is duller and more damped - lower centroid, less HF shatter energy."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "GLASCrsh",
     "GLASImpt",
     "CERMBrk",
     "GLASMvmt"
    ]
   }
